##What happened to the Chinese after the Wuhan outbreak was reported globally?

MICRO-SIGNAL YITIAOTV

Feature description, a short original video every day, every day to tell a moving story, every day selected human beauty, every day to live a better life with me.

Data Source: real-time tracking of new crown pneumonia in tencent

As of 6:00 a.m. on 1 February, the epidemic situation in overseas countries

As at 6 a.m. on 1 February,

More than 11,180 cases of new-type pneumonia have been confirmed nationwide,

A total of 124 cases were confirmed in overseas countries.

On January 31st the China Standard Time announced that

The Chinese epidemic was classified as an "international public health emergency" ,

This is the highest level of alert the WHO can issue,

Only six times since 2009.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
World Health Organization home page

Based on the current outbreak,

The WHO made eight recommendations to China:

1. Timely and comprehensive dissemination of information on the epidemic, including the progress of the epidemic, prevention methods, and Response Policies and measures;
2. Strengthen the response measures to the epidemic situation to curb the development of the current epidemic situation;
3. To ensure the proper functioning of the health system and to protect the health care and other workers;
4. Strengthen surveillance and active screening of the epidemic throughout the country
5. Work with WHO and other partners to conduct research on the epidemiology and control of the disease;
6. Sharing data on human cases
7. Continue to identify the source of the outbreak and potential routes of transmission;
8. Conduct travel checks at international airports and ports to identify symptomatic travellers early for further assessment and treatment to minimize the impact on international traffic.

Chinese in Brazil raised 20,000 masks, launched an online appeal, and waited at the airport for a "Human Express" to return from Brazil

Chinese in Japan donate to refueling in Wuhan

Since the number of confirmed cases was released on January 20,

Chinese people all over the world have been busy,

Prepare donations and donations, especially protective materials such as face masks,

Wuhan University, North American Alumni,

The first time for Wuhan Collection of Medical Supplies;

Yes. The Chinese took a mask factory in Germany

All the inventory has been moved to China;

In "mask power" Japan,

The Chinese tried every means to take the mask back.

An interview with three Chinese in the United States, Japan and Germany,

To hear what they had seen and heard about the outbreak in the area.

Editor Chen Ziwen Qiu Yu

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Be Strong China" flashed on the Nasdaq in New York's Times Square Wednesday, allegedly launched by a chinese-backed media company

Narrator: Angela Shen chaste

She is 32 years old and works in simultaneous interpretation and executive training

San Francisco Bay area, Northern California

The World Health Organization has sounded its highest alarm

At noon on January 30(US time) , WHO declared the outbreak an "international public health emergency" (PHEIC) .

Because of the outbreak, many Americans first learned about the city.

I work in Silicon Valley as a simultaneous interpreter. Since the 22nd, I have been watching WHO live and helping translate the summary into my friends'circle.

WHO released a statement on the 23rd, did not define the Chinese epidemic as PHEIC. The confirmation on the 30th is believed to have mixed feelings among many Chinese.

Because if it does, it will cause many countries and regions around the world to further justify restrictions on China's trade and exports, and further suspend or cancel shipping and flights, and the economic impact will be greater and more far-reaching than it is now.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
WHO convenes a meeting to discuss the new outbreak of pneumonia, photo WHO / C. Black

But the W.H.O.'s statement, which repeatedly stressed China's amazing speed of response and ability to fight, set a new level of anti-epidemic.

The decision is aimed at supporting other, smaller, less resistant countries and urging them not to impose unnecessary restrictions, such as blanket visa restrictions or quarantines for healthy people..

The WHO also commented on the recent suspension of some international flights: Many flights have been reduced or suspended because of a drop in demand rather than a virus, and the WHO can not control whether it can persuade them, but will continue to communicate with people, we hope there will be no unnecessary restrictions.

Now is to wait for the response of countries, hope to be calm and restraint to listen to WHO recommendations..

All kinds of fund-raising messages spread among the Chinese people

Donations to the University of Florida

Chinese-americans haven't been idle since the outbreak figures were released

I'm from Shanghai, have been in the United States for more than seven years, and now live in San Francisco Bay Area, where about a third of my community is Chinese.

January 17-18, I was at Stanford doing the same biography, there were a lot of Chinese participants, there was no outbreak of concern, there was no concern. It wasn't until Jan. 20, when academician Zhong Nanshan appeared to confirm the transmission, that people began to pay close attention.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As of January 31, the CDC announced the official website of the United States new crown pneumonia epidemic

Information on the country's first confirmed case was available on January 21, and in Washington state, the young man was discharged from the hospital shortly after being diagnosed, possibly because of his immune system.

As of January 31, CDC has officially confirmed six new cases of pneumonia in the United States. Most were Chinese with a history of contact in Wuhan, either returning to the United States to attend school or work, or to see their children, and privacy protections in the United States do not allow the identification of names or ages.

All the 3M masks in the supermarket were sold out by the Chinese, and the Internet was full of out of stock

The Chinese on the American side have been busy since the outbreak began. Donations have been so high that 3m masks in big city supermarkets are all sold out.

Many silicon valley companies help employees "match donations" by giving the same amount of money to their employees.

Donations in the United States are required to be made to a registered non-profit organization, 501(C)3, which is very transparent and will provide real-time updates on the status and use of funds.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A group of Chinese volunteers in Silicon Valley delivered 200,000 surgical masks, 27,500 pairs of gloves and 4,000 protective clothing through the largest international nonprofit organization in the United States, with the assistance of alumni associations from universities in Hubei Province, on China Standard Time, signed for by the Wuhan Union Hospital.

I participated in the donation sponsored by the Chinese students and Scholars Association in Berkeley. As of the first two days, the donation stopped and more than $80,000 was raised to buy masks and protective clothing.

Another personal donation I was involved in, by a doctor himself, with a number of domestic partners on the front lines, has raised more than $20,000 to buy protective clothing.

Some of the logistics and shipping resources of the Chinese, has been docking, said that free charter flights to send materials back to China and so on.

American experts and the Government do not recommend wearing masks in the United States photo: Qiao Bao reporter Wu Zhuoming

The epidemic in the United States: objective reporting, calm restraint

But with the announcement of the PHEIC, the wind could change

The U.S. flu itself is pretty bad this year.

The other day I had a slight cold and went out wearing a mask. I went to the dry cleaner near my home. The boss asked me in a panic as soon as he saw it. "Back from China? " I quickly said no, it was flu flu in America!

From what I have seen and heard, the news reports and public opinion in the United States as a whole are very objective. The mainstream media gave objective accounts of the epidemic in China, and the United States Department of Commerce Secretary made a point of standing up during a meeting to pay tribute to the Chinese who died of the new form of pneumonia.

The host of The popular US talk Show, The Daily Show, made a point of commenting on The outbreak, boasting that only China can build a hospital with 10,000 beds in 10 days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Professor Lipkin

Some experts, such as W. Lan Lipkin, a professor of Epidemiology at Columbia University known as the "virus hunter, " traveled to China in 2003 to help with SARS, and to Wuhan on Jan. 28.

But it remains to be seen what the United States will do after the WHO declares the outbreak a PHEIC. On Jan. 30, for example, the day the WHO announced, the U.S. government changed its travel warning for China to level 4, the highest level: Don't go.

Flights between the United States and China, as of January 31, US time, from news reports and asked friends to verify:

US Airways: grounded from January 31 until March 27;

Delta: Plans to wait until February 6 to suspend operations, but the suspension will last until April 30;

United Airlines announces fewer flights, but won't ground them.

American hospital notices

Civil word, the United States epidemic prevention propaganda work or done pretty well, the CDC official website has a series of multilingual defense measures. All the major hospitals have also posted notices, said that if it is from Wuhan, there are symptoms to call the hospital, in the doctor's advice to take measures.

Once there was a group discussion about the US government chartering a plane to pick up American citizens from Hubei, paying $1,000 of their own money, and then the news that there was no food or drink on the plane, and we all joked that we were always cheap.

When the charter plane landed at San Francisco's SFO International Airport, San Franciscans reacted strongly, but the mayor later disagreed. The decision was made to land at a small airfield in Ontario, southern California, and to land at a nearby military base for screening. But the US did not ask to be sent to an island for a two-week quarantine, as the Australian government did.

Street view of San Francisco

"We're fighting the virus, not the Chinese. "

I now get up every day is to start to brush the domestic situation, greetings to family and friends, will also forward docking some resources.

Because California is already the most Chinese state. Many famous schools, social organizations, have canceled the Spring Festival gala, such as Silicon Valley's most famous Stanford, Berkeley, two universities Spring Festival gala, Google employees organized "singing and dancing" , have volunteered to refund tickets to everyone.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chinatown

I have a schoolgirl who lives in the eastern United States. She just returned from the Spring Festival in Shanghai and shared with me:

"Our campus sends out letters saying that students who have recently returned from China do not need to be quarantined as long as they do not have symptoms. I wrote to my daughter's school and told them that we had just come back from China, and the principal told me that he wanted her to come back as soon as possible, and that she didn't need to wear a mask, otherwise the other kids would ask questions and she might feel bad."

But there are also private high schools in California that have told students returning to China not to return to the United States for the time being and to teach themselves; the University of California, San Diego, which has 5,600 Chinese students, is only telling students, avoid going to China if you don't need to. It's interesting to see what these schools do and what impact they have.

In another letter, which has been widely circulated in Chinese circles, the last two paragraphs are moving:

"everyone gets sick, so don't isolate the Chinese, and anyone you think has a connection to China, and don't discriminate against the sick, because that would make the sick ashamed of being sick, and hide their illness, and not protect others.

We're fighting the virus, not the Chinese. The more in times of crisis, the more calm, rational, human, united."

The San Francisco Bay Area of pure living

Let's hope the outbreak dissipates soon, and we can all have a peaceful spring.

Hope that natural and man-made disasters are no longer, so that the country's economic development and adjustment for a few years. But the combination of governance capabilities and emergency systems does provide an opportunity for further upgrading.

There are some domestic friends are small and medium-sized business owners, I hope they can survive this period.

I hope Yangchun can have a major breakthrough in March, in the Qingming Festival do not let more people sad heartache.

Hope to see the Cherry Blossoms in Wuhan in the spring, to their loss of GDP, to contribute a modest effort.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Currently four confirmed cases in Germany are admitted to the hospital on site, Schwabin Hospital, Munich

Narrator: Tang Jie

30 + , architect

Munich, Germany

On the morning of January 29th, the COVID-19 soon confirmed its first case in Germany, and it turned out to be a German.

It is reported that a Chinese colleague from the Chinese branch of a German company came to Germany for a meeting and infected the German in the form of human-to-human transmission. The Chinese compatriot is also not from Wuhan, but from Shanghai, because her parents visited her from Wuhan before she came to Germany. And so it went from person to person, and the first case of COVID-19 was diagnosed, in my city, Munich. The patient was quarantined at Schwabing Hospital, two subway stations from my home.

Just a few hours later, as I was writing this late that night, three more Germans were diagnosed with the infection, all of them among the more than 40 colleagues of the first infected person who had been shot.

In a single day on January 29th, Germany, with four cases, overtook France with three to become Europe's most affected country. (as of 6:00 China Standard Time 1 February, 7 new cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in Germany and 6 in France.)

A notice about the coronavirus has been posted at Berlin airport in Germany

And at the same time the news, Germany decided to send a plane to evacuate overseas Chinese from China on the 30th, is really speed.

It never rains but it pours. I think the German media will fry again after that, just like the closing down of Wuhan, the momentum unleashed by the German media. Of course, the first to be hit is the Chinese like me in Germany.

This morning in the elevator, I and a porter accidentally met, he first pressed, I pressed up, did not expect the elevator does not follow the rules slowly began to go up. We looked at each other awkwardly. He quickly asked me, are you Chinese? I said yes. He immediately shouted, "mother, coronavirus! " And immediately hid his nose and mouth in the collar of his coat, exaggerated but serious. On the top floor, I got off the elevator, and on my way out, I lost the phrase, Alles Gute! (all is well!)

I've heard so many examples of this happening overseas these days. Because of this virus, the Chinese have become the Wuhan people in Germany. We will go through the same thing, and perhaps worse, under the care of foreigners.

On the afternoon of January 30, "we no longer have masks" was written in Chinese in front of a pharmacy in Germany

A few days ago in Nuremberg under the reminder of a Chinese friend, in the online order mask, but delay delivery, so decided to go to the pharmacy to try their luck.

German pharmacies abound, but several visited and were told that masks were sold out. Even some stores you a door, see you are Chinese, do not have to speak, the salesperson will take the initiative to tell you: no mask. It's simple, it saves each other time.

I went there more and figured out what it was like. Judging by their attitude and tone, some pharmacies do not have masks, but do not sell them to the Chinese. Think also right, because once the mask into a strategic material, then they must be priority for the use of locals, after all, "landlords do not have surplus food. ".

In the past few weeks, when the domestic epidemic broke out, the overseas childe of the world with the spirit of "one side is in trouble, eight sides support" , with the speed of lightning, bought up the world's masks, Germany is not immune.

It is said that the German Alumni Association of a school in the south of the country has moved all the stocks of the German Dach mask factory to China, so if the epidemic is to spread in Europe, it is estimated that the gap in masks in Germany is also very large.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Inside the University of Heidelberg

In fact, the German health habits, has been "heartless" style, really not good.

I often see them eating half of a loaf of bread and accidentally drop it on the floor without patting it, or eating an apple straight away after buying it from a supermarket, ripping off the label and rubbing it on their sleeves, this "wild" habit has always made me feel inferior.

As for masks, I think that Germans who can't stand the rain and the umbrellas, wearing masks may kill them more than the virus. So I can imagine the future on the streets, of Chinese people wearing masks, showing up with their own BGM.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As of 0600 hours on China Standard Time, Germany had confirmed its seventh case of new pneumonia. The Ministry of Health in Bavaria, Germany, January 29 local time announced: Germany previously confirmed four patients, have no clinical symptoms of new coronary pneumonia. If the virus test is negative for two consecutive days, you can leave the hospital.

But the good news is that Germany's "fine tradition" of doctors not prescribing drugs to patients, even when they have a headache, may have objectively raised German resistance. It's like last year when I was home with a fever for a week, in bed for two weeks, feeling like I was going to die, and the doctor told me to drink more water, and then refused to give me any medicine. Unexpectedly I also in this long and tedious in "The resurrection" . So "wild" may also have "wild" benefits.

As for how the entire German health system, will behave in the face of such a virus, I do not know, wait and see.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Only dare stick in the home of homemade Spring Festival couplets

Narrator: Xu Chenyou

23 years old, average I.T. Guy

Tokyo, Japan

My girlfriend and I live in Tokyo, I work, she studies, the Japanese Spring Festival holiday, so we can not go back.

There wasn't much of a Spring Festival atmosphere in Japan. I wrote a Spring Festival couplet and stuck it on the door. When my girlfriend came home, she pointed it at my nose and scolded me: What if our neighbors knew we were Chinese and separated us. All right, well, stick it in the door.

The biggest impact of the outbreak on me was the increased use of mobile phone traffic. Every day at work are uncertain, a time to fish to see how the epidemic.

Japanese colleagues will also ask us about China's situation, but most of the concern about the epidemic is Chinese, after all, their families are still in the country. Now my daily task is to video chat with the family elders, "pull gang gang" to give them the knowledge of prevention of the epidemic.

The Human Resources Department of the company is crazy busy. Not to mention whether the colleagues returning from the Spring Festival will be able to return, the employees returning from China to Japan have to go to the medical examination first. After the medical examination results come out, they can come back to work. Many meetings have to be postponed. But the company said it understood, saying it was a safety measure, which in turn comforted those of us who continued to work.

There are a lot of Chinese in our company, people who have never worn masks before, now wear them all day in the office.

Yesterday to the company downstairs to eat Chinese food, the shop owner in Shanghai also began to wear a mask, this wave of infectious disease prevention awareness is really in place.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Japan Post Office posted a statement saying: "International Express delivery to mainland China and Hong Kong, China will be temporarily suspended. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Face masks sold out in Japanese drugstores

I was in a "mask country" , trying to send some back to my friends and relatives, but I couldn't get them. The mask cabinets in the drug stores and convenience stores were all empty.

Finally in the residential area of the supermarket to buy some, want to use EMS to speed up the return, the results of international express have stopped, only slow delivery, can not help but also very helpless.

Now the Chinese in Japan are trying to find ways to get a mask back to their friends in China.

Although the language school my girlfriend attends is full of Chinese students, it doesn't seem to make a difference. Is that the students are wearing masks in class, today the school also gave each class has been issued disinfectant, into the classroom before the queue disinfection, reminiscent of the SARS period.

She had a classmate studying at a university in Wuhan who was miserable. In order to take the postgraduate entrance examination this year, he had to go back to the university in March to prepare his application materials. After a year of studying for the exam, I'd be devastated if I couldn't take the summer exam because I couldn't go back.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
News of the outbreak from Academician Zhong Nanshan is being broadcast on Japanese TV

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
NHK news was showing a video of Chinese people playing Ping Pong in the living room

I now watch TV in the evening and every news station is broadcasting the report of the epidemic, but it is very objective, and there is no media that deliberately magnifies the bad places, NHK even shows the news of Chinese people enjoying themselves at home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Japanese TBS broadcasts the news with the micro-blog content as the material

However, when the epidemic first came out, many Japanese media tried hard to pick up the intelligence on Weibo, and there were also many news footage that directly captured the content posted by ordinary people on Weibo, which was half true and half false, and could not be laughed or cried.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare press conference, Jnn

As the outbreak grew, on January 29th the Japanese government finally moved to charter a flight to bring home the Japanese stranded in Wuhan.

Of the 206 Japanese who were among the first to return, three were found to be infected with COVID-19.

Nine of the 210 in the second flight on January 30 had symptoms such as cough and fever.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Left: Chinese netizens apologizing inside the Red Box, right: Japanese netizens comforting the Chinese netizen

Of course, the Internet is full of Japanese who talk too much, but most scold the Japanese government for not paying attention. Those who pick them up have to pay 80,000 yen (more than 5,000 yuan) in taxes, and they are not kept in isolation.

The Chinese apologized on twitter, and the Japanese replied, you're right, China's right, the Japanese government is too slow.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
January 30,10:44 by Minoru Kumasaki, Tokyo News, on a government chartered flight from Wuhan to Tokyo International Airport

It should be quite a lot of people worried about cross-infection inside the plane, quote a paragraph from Tokyo Medical University, Tatsu Hada Medical Professional, I hope you can be reassured.

"Although we expect to have infected people on this chartered flight back to Japan, we hope that people do not fear the spread of the virus in Japan.

In an airplane, where the air flows from above to below and is constantly ventilated, it is difficult to spread COVID-19, so it is difficult to catch the virus just by flying on the same plane.

But we can't underestimate the virus. We have the Olympics this year, and it's imperative that we get it under control."

We also call on other countries to give the same political and technological attention as China, which will help us to stop the spread of the disease as soon as possible."

In the words of the headmaster, the more times of crisis, the more need for calm, reason, humanity, unity.

I hope Wuhan will get out of the predicament as soon as possible with the help of the whole country and overseas Chinese. I hope China will get better and better.
